article.headline: USC-Upstate claims 3rd seed, beats ETSU 79-73
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- Ricardo Glenn scored 24 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and South Carolina-Upstate beat East Tennessee State, 79-73 Friday night to claim the No. 3 seed into the Atlantic Sun tournament in the regular season finale for both schools. USC-Upstate (18-13, 11-7) will host a tournament quarterfinal contest March 4. Rashawn Rembert converted a pair of free throws and drained a 3-pointer in the final minute to pull the Buccaneers within two, 75-73 with 43 seconds left, but ETSU could not score again and USC-Upstate padded its lead from the free throw line. Jodd Maxey added 19 points while the Spartans shot a crisp 51.9 percent from the field (28 of 54). East Tennessee State (17-14, 10-8) must await the results of Saturday's remaining conference games to learn its seed for the tournament.
